# Content Production Batch Standards

## Weekly Content Volume

Every week in a production batch must match the channel configuration defined in `brand/brand_config.json` `channel_config`. The default structure is:

| Channel | Pieces per Week | Format |
|---------|----------------|--------|
| [Channel 1] | [N] | [Format description] |
| [Channel 2] | [N] | [Format description] |
| [Channel 3] | [N] | [Format description] |

Update this table to match your `channel_config` after integration.

Derivative content (e.g., short-form clips from podcast/video) is not net-new creation. Clip count varies organically; do not force clips to hit a number.

## File Naming Convention

```
week-N-channel-slug.md
week-N-channel-N.md
```

Examples:
```
week-1-blog-topic-slug.md
week-1-linkedin-1.md through week-1-linkedin-3.md (or match your brand's LinkedIn volume; Capable Wealth uses 3 + optional native video)
week-1-facebook-1.md through week-1-facebook-5.md
week-1-podcast-topic-slug.md
week-1-clip-1.md through week-1-clip-5.md
```

## File Template (All Content Types)

1. **Title** (H1)
2. **Post Metadata** -- Type, Week, Theme, Quarterly plan reference, Strategic context, Story classifications used
3. **Visual Assets** -- Image type, Rationale, AI image prompt (9-point standard, brand palette only), Text overlay, Platform/dimensions
4. **Clip Extraction Map** (podcast/video scripts only) -- 2-5 clip candidates with source segment, hook line, core insight, platform tags, estimated duration
5. **Full content draft** -- Voice owner's voice per voice-profile.md and content-recipe.md
6. **Quality Checklist** -- Voice Alignment, Audience Specificity, Relevance Validation, Pull Signal Design, Visual Assets, Content Integrity, Compliance

## Image Type Variety

Each week's social posts must use a mix of visual styles. A feed of identical cards is not acceptable.

| Post # | Required Image Type |
|--------|-------------------|
| 1 of 5 | Stat highlight card OR quote card |
| 2 of 5 | Conceptual photograph (photorealistic) |
| 3 of 5 | Simple infographic or data visualization |
| 4 of 5 | Conceptual photograph (different subject from #2) |
| 5 of 5 | Any type not already used this week |

Hard rules:
- Max 1 text-on-block card per 5 posts per platform per week
- Conceptual photographs must be photorealistic, never cartoon or illustrated
- Each week's images must look visually distinct when viewed as a set

## Social Post Expansion

When the quarterly plan briefs fewer posts than the channel requires, create additional posts by:
- Isolating individual talking points from anchor content as standalone insights
- Creating story-driven variations
- Adding action prompts or engagement questions
- Building week-to-week narrative continuity

## Content Integrity

Before drafting any content, read `brand/experience-inventory.md`. All client stories, experience claims, and case studies must comply with the Content Integrity Filter (content-recipe.md Section 5.1).

Key requirements:
- Every story must be classified as `[REAL-ANONYMIZED]`, `[ILLUSTRATIVE]`, or `[GENERAL-PRINCIPLE]`
- Classifications must be listed in Post Metadata
- Illustrative examples must use approved framing language
- If the experience inventory is unpopulated, all stories default to `[ILLUSTRATIVE]`
